{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"I managed to get something working once using [SplineCurve3](https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/blob\/master\/src\/extras\/core\/Curve.js#L709). I don't think were I left the code though. But that didn't solved the rotation. I think the rotation can be done by using the previous point and the current point. Like in the birds example. Maybe @zz85 knows how to use this in the right way?\n","created_at":"2011-11-11T02:11:39.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/743#issuecomment-2704128","id":2704128,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/743","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI3MDQxMjg=","updated_at":"2011-11-11T02:11:39.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/2704128","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"I can't see the image but yes, i think this is what the curve classes are for, and rotation can use `curve.getTangent()` (just updated to make it work with SplineCurve3)\n\n``` javascript\nmesh.position = spline.getPoint(t);\nmesh.rotation = spline.getTangent(t);\n```\n\nspline could be any curve3 classes eg. `THREE.LineCurve3`, `THREE.QuadraticBezierCurve3`, `THREE.CubicBezierCurve3`, and `THREE.SplineCurve3`\n\n``` javascript\nvar randomPoints = [];\n\nfor ( var i = 0; i < 100; i ++ ) {\n\n    randomPoints.push(\n        new THREE.Vector3(Math.random() * 4000 - 2000, Math.random() * 4000 - 2000, Math.random() * 4000 - 2000)\n    );\n\n}\n\nspline = new THREE.SplineCurve3(randomPoints);\n```\n","created_at":"2011-11-11T03:26:17.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/743#issuecomment-2704541","id":2704541,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/743","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI3MDQ1NDE=","updated_at":"2011-11-11T03:29:32.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/2704541","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/314997?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/zz85","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMxNDk5Nw==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"zz85","type":"User","id":314997,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Thank both of you very much for the quick reply! I really appreciate your awesome work!\n\n@zz85, just regarding your code your answer seems very logical. :-) I created a very short example to test it but it fails:\n\n``` javascript\nvar spline = new THREE.SplineCurve3([\n    new THREE.Vector3(-20,  0, 0),\n    new THREE.Vector3(  0, 20, 0),\n    new THREE.Vector3( 20,  0, 0)\n]);\n\nconsole.log(spline.getPoint(0.5));\nconsole.log(spline.getTangent(0.5));\n```\n\nThe console prints the following error:\n\n``` javascript\nTHREE.Vector3\n  x: 0\n  y: 20\n  z: 0\n  __proto__: Object\n\nThree.js:373 Uncaught TypeError: Object [object Object] has no method 'unit'\n  THREE.Curve.getTangent\n  (anonymous function)\n```\n\nSo getPoint() works and the getTangent()-method exists but runs into an error. I was using _r45_. Do I need a more recent version of Three.js (if there is one) or will the code need to be fixed? :-)\n\nKind regards and thank you again!\n","created_at":"2011-11-11T17:02:12.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/743#issuecomment-2710419","id":2710419,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/743","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI3MTA0MTk=","updated_at":"2011-11-12T11:54:53.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/2710419","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ymmd\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ymmd\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1186931?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ymmd","g